<taxonomicName box="[1019,1150,1652,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Macrolycus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1150,1652,1676]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">Macrolycus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the tetraschistic apex of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[435,519,1687,1711]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[487,519,1687,1711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1580,2036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[199,465,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
Description (
<typeStatus box="[351,452,1724,1748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Body medium-sized, black, pronotum and elytra testaceous brown (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1353,1724,1748]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,258,1858,1879]" captionTargetBox="[192,1357,189,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,174,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. General appearance of holotype: 23. Macrolycus ligulatus sp. nov.; 24. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 25. M. extrusus sp. nov.; 26. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 27. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 28. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 29. M. venustus sp. nov.; 30. M. luteus sp. nov. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280381/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1321,1353,1724,1748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head small, with prominent antennal tubercles. Antennomeres 
<number box="[800,814,1759,1783]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[871,885,1759,1783]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
lamellate (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1098,1759,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1066,1098,1759,1783]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum transverse, lateral margins parallel-sided, anterior angles blunt and acute, posterior angles acutely projected; anterior and lateral margins of pronotum orange, with prominent rib; posterior margin sinuate (
<figureCitation box="[948,1032,1831,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,258,1858,1879]" captionTargetBox="[192,1357,189,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,174,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. General appearance of holotype: 23. Macrolycus ligulatus sp. nov.; 24. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 25. M. extrusus sp. nov.; 26. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 27. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 28. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 29. M. venustus sp. nov.; 30. M. luteus sp. nov. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280381/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1000,1032,1831,1855]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum dark brown, emarginate posteriorly. Elytra subparallel, with prominent glabrous humeri. Elytral costa 
<number box="[1016,1030,1868,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
stout at humeri, shortened, reaching at most third of elytral length, costa 
<number box="[557,571,1903,1927]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching to anterior two thirds of elytra, costae 
<number box="[1109,1123,1903,1927]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[1178,1192,1903,1927]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
stouter and more elevated, glabrous. Costal interspaces with irregular punctures, covered with dense soft testaceous pubescence. Aedeagus with short robust paramerae, median lobe with tetraschistic apex, prominent lateral rib and broad ventral cavity (
<figureCitation box="[234,365,2012,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="54">
Figs 
<number box="[291,365,2012,2036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="54" value="41.42">41, 42</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[199,1301,151,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[199,369,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">Measurements.</emphasis>
Length 12.1 mm, width at humeri 2.95 mm, pronotum length/width 1.95/2.00 mm. 
<emphasis box="[199,343,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[350,417,188,212]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">China</collectingCountry>
(Sichuan); the species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[945,993,189,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[199,1301,151,248]" box="[199,1282,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[199,325,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the tetraschistic apex of the median lobe of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,754,331,358]" box="[151,754,331,358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,508,331,358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
