<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,402,966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[199,320,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by the shape of the male genitalia, whose median lobe is apically constricted in the bottle-neck shape (
<figureCitation box="[528,613,510,534]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[581,613,510,534]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
). The apical part of the aedeagus is not inflated as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1222,1328,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Macrolycus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1328,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">M. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[220,305,546,570]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[273,305,546,570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,402,966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[199,453,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Description (
<typeStatus box="[347,445,582,606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
)
</emphasis>
. Body small, slender and dark brown; pronotum and elytra testaceous; margins of pronotum orange, central part brown (
<figureCitation box="[549,635,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,258,1858,1879]" captionTargetBox="[192,1357,189,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,174,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. General appearance of holotype: 23. Macrolycus ligulatus sp. nov.; 24. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 25. M. extrusus sp. nov.; 26. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 27. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 28. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 29. M. venustus sp. nov.; 30. M. luteus sp. nov. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280381/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[603,635,618,642]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head small, with conspicuous antennal tubercles. Antennae overlapping midlength of elytra when inclined, from antennomere 
<number box="[825,839,654,678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="3.0">3</number>
lamellate (
<figureCitation box="[966,1052,654,678]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[1020,1052,654,678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum almost quadrate, with acute posterior angles; hind margin sinuate, protruding posteriad (
<figureCitation box="[902,988,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,258,1858,1879]" captionTargetBox="[192,1357,189,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,174,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 30. General appearance of holotype: 23. Macrolycus ligulatus sp. nov.; 24. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 25. M. extrusus sp. nov.; 26. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 27. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 28. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 29. M. venustus sp. nov.; 30. M. luteus sp. nov. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280381/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[956,988,690,714]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum dark brown, parallel sided, with straight posterior margin. Elytra subparallel, with costae 
<number box="[876,890,726,750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[952,966,726,750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="4.0">4</number>
stout; costae 
<number box="[1131,1145,726,750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[1207,1221,726,750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="3.0">3</number>
relatively weaker, becoming inconspicuous behind humeri. Pubescence testaceous, dense, decumbent. Aedeagus relatively short and robust, without paramerae; apical part of aedeagus vase-like; apex of aedeagus with small notch and ventrally inclined lamella (
<figureCitation box="[345,476,834,858]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 54" captionStartId="8.[151,258,1689,1710]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[152,1434,194,1668]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 54. Male genitalia of holotype: 31. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov., lateral view, 32. same, ventral view; 33. M. ligulatus sp. nov., lateral view, 34. same, apex of median lobe; 35. M. luteus sp. nov., lateral view, 36. same, ventral view; 37. M. mucronatus sp. nov., lateral view, 38. same, ventral view; 39. M. muyuensis sp. nov., lateral view, 40. same, ventral view; 41. M. quadrifidus sp. nov., lateral view, 42. same, apical part of median lobe; 43. M. rubineus sp. nov., lateral view, 44. same, ventral view; 45. M. venustus sp. nov., lateral view, 46. same, ventral view. The male antennomeres of holotype: 47. Macrolycus extrusus sp. nov.; 48. M. ligulatus sp. nov.; 49. M. luteus sp. nov.; 50. M. mucronatus sp. nov.; 51. M. muyuensis sp. nov.; 52. M. quadrifidus sp. nov.; 53. M. rubineus sp. nov.; 54. M. venustus sp. nov. Scales 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280382/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
Figs 
<number box="[402,476,834,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55" value="43.44">43, 44</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,402,966]" box="[199,1301,870,895]" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[199,369,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="55">Measurements.</emphasis>
